<Recipe name="FC Post">
	<About>
		<description>
This recipe demonstrates common Anteater commands for array manipulation, conditional logic, and
output. It covers variable creation, array operations, conditionals, and string replacement. The
recipe provides practical examples of how to define and output variables, sort arrays, get array
size, access specific array elements, check for the existence of values within arrays, and perform
string replacement. Additionally, it illustrates the use of conditional statements to perform logic
based on computed values. This recipe is suitable for users looking to understand foundational
Anteater scripting techniques for workflow automation and data processing. The examples provided
are modular and can be adapted to a wide range of scenarios, making this recipe a useful reference
for both new and experienced Anteater users. Step-by-step, the recipe demonstrates best practices
for handling arrays and strings, performing validation, and structuring scripts in a clear and
organized manner, with explicit output after each key operation to aid in debugging and
comprehension. Furthermore, the recipe highlights error handling in array operations, demonstrates
dynamic value checks, and showcases how to perform both in-place variable updates and conditional
branching for robust script logic. By following this recipe, users will gain insights into efficient
Anteater script design, enabling them to automate repetitive tasks, validate data flows, and handle
exceptions gracefully within their automated workflows.
		</description> 
		<author name="Anteater Example Author" email="example.author@anteater.com" messager="Slack: @anteater_author" phone="+1000000000" /> 
	</About> 
	<Var name="greeting" value="Hello, World!" /> 
	<Out name="greeting" /> 
	<Var name="numbers" type="array">
		<item>3</item> 
		<item>1</item> 
		<item>2</item> 
	</Var> 
	<Sort name="numbers" order="asc" /> 
	<Out name="numbers" /> 
	<ArraySize name="numbers" result="size" /> 
	<Out name="size" /> 
	<ArrayElement name="array" index="1" /> 
	<Out name="array::1" /> 
	<CheckInArray name="numbers" value="2" onErrorMsg="2 not found!" /> 
	<Out>Number 2 exists in the array.</Out> 
	<Var name="text" value="Hello, Anteater!" /> 
	<Replace name="text" search="Anteater" replace="World" /> 
	<Out name="text" /> 
	<If value="$var{size}" equals="3">
		<Out>The array has exactly 3 elements.</Out> 
		<Else>
			<Out>Array size is not 3.</Out> 
		</Else> 
	</If> 
	<Var name="count" value="0" /> 
	<While name="count" notEqual="5">
		<Out name="count" /> 
		<Inc name="count" /> 
	</While> 
	<Out>Loop completed!</Out> 
</Recipe> 
